<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="395" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1775,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,1955,1982]" pageId="4" pageNumber="395">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body oblong, pronotum with narrow and uniseriate paranota, hood entirely convering head and pronotum from above, except posterior process. Hemelytra with costal area regularly biseriate and subcostal area narrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
